The article is a proclamation issued by President Barack Obama on October 15, 2009, declaring it as White Cane Safety Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of providing full inclusion and equal opportunities for blind and visually impaired individuals in society. It highlights the significance of the white cane as a symbol of freedom, independence, and mobility for blind Americans. The proclamation also mentions the commitment of the administration to ensure access to education and employment for blind individuals, as well as the development of assistive technologies. The president encourages the improvement of Braille literacy and acknowledges the contributions made by blind and visually impaired individuals to the nation. The proclamation concludes by calling upon all Americans to observe White Cane Safety Day with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.